# Refactoring Four_Component to use KnowledgeNode

## Problem
In a previous iteration, [ArchNode](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/ArchModels.js#35-92) properties (`dependencies`, `dependents`, metadata) were merged directly into [Four_Component](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#466-519). This violated the separation of concerns: the **WDL Table Graph** (Four_Row, Five_Choice) became tightly coupled with the **Knowledge/Architecture Graph** (ArchNode).

## Solution
Create `KnowledgeNode` (which extends [ArchNode](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/ArchModels.js#35-92)) and make it a **member variable** of [Four_Component](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#466-519). This unifies the Decomposition and Recomposition nodes while keeping the knowledge filing system separate from the UI routing system.

---

## 1. Create `KnowledgeNode`

Create `models/KnowledgeNode.js`:
```javascript
import { ArchNode } from './ArchModels.js';

export class KnowledgeNode extends ArchNode {
    constructor(id, label, description = "") {
        super(id, label, description);
        this.rawJsonResponse = null;   // Full parsedJsonObj from LLM
        this.mermaidGraph = "";        // generateCausalityMermaid() output
        this.hopRegId = null;          // generateOntoHop() Hop RegId
        // `dependencies` and `dependents` are inherited from ArchNode!
    }
}
```

---

## 2. Strip [ArchNode](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/ArchModels.js#35-92) from [Four_Component](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#466-519)

In [models/WISH.js](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js):
1. Remove all [ArchNode](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/ArchModels.js#35-92) properties (`dependents`, `dependencies`, `isProcessed`, `order_of_appearance`, etc.) from [Four_Component](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#466-519) constructor.
2. Initialize `this.knowledgeNode = new KnowledgeNode(this.RegId, nam);` in the constructor.
3. Remove [addDependency](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#484-493) and [removeDependency](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/ArchModels.js#70-80) methods from [Four_Component](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#466-519) (they will now be called on `this.knowledgeNode`).
4. Update [destructor()](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#501-510), [is_a_parent_System](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#511-514), and [is_a_Leaf_node](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/WDL_2026March23/models/WISH.js#515-518) to check `this.knowledgeNode.dependencies`.

